  "translations": {
    "en": {
      "description": {
        "text": "A superb sport climbing crag with high-quality routes for climbers of all abilities, though it is particularly challenging for those climbing at the harder grades. The rock is solid, reddish granite. The climbing is varied, with vertical, slabby and overhanging terrain, and the routes are up to 20 m high. Unfortunately, the crag has yet to be discovered by sport climbers, but it is set for a renaissance. Scrub and several trees have been removed, allowing sun, light and air to reach the rock. Mellanväggen has reopened, with several routes in the easier grades. Ingmar Petterson’s overhanging wall, formerly known as boulderväggen, has been re-equipped and cleaned. It is named after Ingmar, who did much to develop climbing in Västervik. The route “Dansa med myggor”, graded 7a, has become the benchmark used by Västervik climbers for grading. All grading at the harder grades is based on it. Jim Wasmuth made the first onsight ascent in the same year that it was established. Climbing pioneer Johan Luhr established the first 8a routes early on, raising the standard among local climbers. The crag faces south-west and gets the sun after 11.00 in summer. The crag has 11 particularly recommended routes.",
        "method": "llm",
        "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
        "sourceIds": [
          "legacy:rasklippan"
        ]
      },
      "sections": {
        "allmant": {
          "title": {
            "text": "General",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:rasklippan"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "A superb sport climbing crag with high-quality routes for climbers of all abilities, though it is particularly challenging in the upper grades. The rock is solid, reddish granite. The climbing is varied, with vertical faces, slabs and overhangs, and routes up to 20 m long. Unfortunately, the crag has yet to be discovered by sport climbers, but it is set for a renaissance. Scrub and several trees have been removed, allowing sun, light and air to reach the rock. Mellanväggen has reopened, with several routes in the easier grades. Ingmar Petterson's overhanging wall, formerly known as Boulderväggen, has been rebolted and cleaned. It is named after Ingmar, who did much to develop climbing in Västervik. The route “Dansa med myggor”, graded 7a, has become the benchmark for grading among Västervik climbers. All grading in the upper grades is based on it. Jim Wasmuth made the first onsight ascent in the same year that the route was established. Climbing pioneer Johan Luhr established the first 8a routes early on, raising the standard among local climbers. The crag faces south-west and gets sun after 11.00 in summer. The crag has 11 particularly recommended routes.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:rasklippan"
            ]
          }
        },
        "vagbeskrivning": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Directions",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:rasklippan"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "The crag lies about 44 km north-west of Västervik. From Västervik, take the E22 towards Gamleby, then head towards Överum. Before Överum, pass the cemetery on your left. Turn left onto the first paved road and drive uphill to the crest, where you turn left and then immediately right downhill, with the sports hall on your left. Park on the gravel area to the left before the playing field. Follow the floodlit trail downhill for 300 m to reach Branta väggen.\n\nThe crag lies about 70 km from Linköping. Take road 35 and continue past Åtvidaberg. In Överum, turn right after the kiosk on your left. Drive uphill, then follow the directions above.\n\nThere are also train services to Överum from Linköping and Västervik. The crag is within walking distance (900 m) of the railway station. Follow the directions above.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:rasklippan"
            ]
          }
        },
        "leder": {
